{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/net.doo.ScanbotSDK\/documentation\/ScanbotSDK"]]},"abstract":[{"text":"Field validation status.","type":"text"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"attribute","text":"@objc"},{"kind":"text","text":"(SBSDKGenericDocumentFieldValidationStatus) "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"final"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"SBSDKGenericDocumentFieldValidationStatus"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["iOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"level":2,"text":"Overview","type":"heading","anchor":"overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Optical character recognition (OCR) invariably introduces errors in the recognized text.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"There are numerous ways to verify that what has been recognized is, in fact, what was","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"written in the document.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The best way to validate the value of a field is for it to have a known format or validation"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"logic. For example, an IBAN number has a known format and two check digits that make it"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"very unlikely that a value with OCR errors will pass validation. Fields with known"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"validation rules will have a validation status of either VALID or INVALID."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Fields whose value can be inferred from other fields, or from domain knowledge (for example,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the field may have the same value in every instance of this type of document), will have the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"status INFERRED. Inferring the value of a field is a strong validation method, provided that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"there are no unexpected changes to the document format."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Fields that do not have validation rules and cannot be inferred can still be validated by checking whether the same"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"value is recognized from multiple attempts, e.g. across multiple frames of a camera stream."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"If the same value is recognized in multiple frames, the value is considered CONFIRMED, otherwise"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"it will have the status NONE. This is the least strict validation method, as it does not protect"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"from systemic OCR errors, but in practice it still provides good results for most fields."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"SBSDKGenericDocumentFieldValidationStatus"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"SBSDKGenericDocumentFieldValidationStatus"}],"modules":[{"name":"ScanbotSDK"}],"symbolKind":"class","title":"SBSDKGenericDocumentFieldValidationStatus","externalID":"c:@M@ScanbotSDK@objc(cs)SBSDKGenericDocumentFieldValidationStatus","role":"symbol","roleHeading":"Class"},"topicSections":[{"generated":true,"title":"Instance Properties","anchor":"Instance-Properties","identifiers":["doc:\/\/net.doo.ScanbotSDK\/documentation\/ScanbotSDK\/SBSDKGenericDocumentFieldValidationStatus\/rawValue"]},{"generated":true,"title":"Type Properties","anchor":"Type-Properties","identifiers":["doc:\/\/net.doo.ScanbotSDK\/documentation\/ScanbotSDK\/SBSDKGenericDocumentFieldValidationStatus\/confirmed","doc:\/\/net.doo.ScanbotSDK\/documentation\/ScanbotSDK\/SBSDKGenericDocumentFieldValidationStatus\/ignored","doc:\/\/net.doo.ScanbotSDK\/documentation\/ScanbotSDK\/SBSDKGene